This being the case, a planned transfer of power, especially the reorganization of the cabinet and the replacement of the party chairman, is necessary. John Major has always been weak and powerless, and vacillates to the left and to the right resulting in his own crisis of honor. After 9 June, John Major will have to answer for all of the disasters, and it is time to use him as a scapegoat. The results of the local elections showed that the Tories were reduced to the third party nationally, behind the Liberal Democrats and the Labour Party. 